50|$|In telecommunication, {{a neutral}} direct-current {{telegraph}} system (single-current system, <b>single-current</b> <b>transmission</b> system, single-Morse system) is a telegraph {{system in which}} (a) current flows during marking intervals and no current flows during spacing intervals for the transmission of signals over a line, and (b) the direction of current flow is immaterial.|$|E

